HEADWORD: Suspectless
<hw>Sus*pect"less</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not
suspecting; having no suspicion.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir T.
Herbert.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not suspected; not mistrusted.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Beau. & Fl.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Suspend</ent>⟦br⟧
